Description: Ibanez RG Iron Label 7 String with Premium RG QM Red Desert Neck + Gator Case Selling my Custom Iron label 7 string with Gator case. -Black Iron Label basswood body with an awesome Premium RG QM Red Desert Neck with offset position dots. -25.5" scale length. -Upgraded Tight-End R bridge. -Seymour Duncan Custom 5 bridge pup with standard Ibanez neck pup. -Single volume pot with a 130k ohm resistor and .002mf capacitor treble bleed installed. -Standard tuning machines. -Dunlop heavy Core .010" - .060" strings, and tuned GDGCFAD. Has two blemishes, a paint chip on the back, and the original Gibraltar bridge screw holes can be seen just outside of the tight-End R bridge. Neither affect playing performance and are not immediately noticeable. This is a great looking, reliable shredder with that "chunky" basswood sustain and tone plus a straight, smooth playing Premium Ibanez neck with nicely rounded factory fret ends!The Gator case is in good condition; it has some scuffs and signs of use, and provides excellent protection. The neck feels solid, plays fast, holds tune and the frets show no visible wear! I've gotten many compliments on this guitar!Please ask any additional questions and thanks for looking!
